4'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2dc4'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2dc4')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2dc4" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>It could also be a selection effect -- if you're doing something even though you're not supposed to, it must be something you really like.</p>

