href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2czj')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2czj" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2czj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Kyre/">Kyre</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 August 2010 05:35:17AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_2czj'>8 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2czj'] = ['7 points', '8 points', '9 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_2czj')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_2czj" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I never read Lovecraft as being any kind of metaphor for the real world, so I wouldn't vote this up as a rationalist quote for that reason.</p>

<p>But I like it as a device used Lovecraft to try to convey a sheer magnitude of horror. Can you imagine discovering something so horrific you wished you could delete the whole thing from your memory ? The more you pride yourself as a rationalist, the more horrific it would have to be.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2czj"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2czj" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2czj')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2czj" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2czj')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2czj" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2jj/rationality_quotes_august_2010/2czj?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2czj" href="#2cxj" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2czj" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2czj')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2czj class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2czj" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_2cxs" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_2cxs" class="parent"><a name="2cxs" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_2cxs" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_2cxs" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_2cxs" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/DSimon/">DSimon</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 August 2010 03:21:28AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_2cxs'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_2cxs')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_2cxs" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_2cxs" href="http